==English==

===Etymology===
Borrowed from German ''[[Flügelhorn]]'', from ''[[Flügel]]'' meaning “[[wing]]”, “[[flank]]” + ''[[Horn]]'' meaning “[[horn]]”

===Noun===
'''flugelhorn'''

#A [[brass]] [[instrument]] resembling a [[cornet]] but with a wider, conical bore, and built on the same in the same B-flat pitch as many [[trumpet]]s and cornets but played with a more deeply conical mouthpiece than those two brass instruments, and usually with three valves and employs the same fingering system as other brass instruments.  

